        Reads the next line from input and return true if a line was read. If no more lines are available in this split, a false is returned.
        Parameters:

      • nextShape

        protected boolean nextShape(V s)
                     throws IOException
        Reads next shape from input and returns true. If no more shapes are left in the split, a false is returned. This function first reads a line by calling the method nextLine(Text) then parses the returned line by calling TextSerializable.fromText(Text) on that line. If no stock shape is set, a NullPointerException is thrown.
        Parameters:
        s - A mutable shape object to update with the next value
        Returns:
        true if an object was read; false if end-of-file was reached.
        Throws:
        IOException - If an error happens while reading from disk
